%20doctor%20after%20her%20military%20service.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20dreamed%20bigger%20or%20worked%20harder%20to%20achieve%20her%20goals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20investigators%20from%20the%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board%20have%20determined%20the%20CRJ700%20airplane%20was%20at%20325%20feet%20(91%20meters)%2C%20plus%20or%20minus%2025%20feet%2C%20at%20the%20time%20of%20impact%2C%20officials%20said%20at%20a%20Saturday%20evening%20news%20briefing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20information%20was%20based%20on%20data%20recovered%20from%20the%20jet's%20flight%20data%20recorder%20-%20the%20%26quot%3Bblack%20box%26quot%3B%20that%20tracks%20the%20aircraft's%20movements%2C%20speed%20and%20other%20parameters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20detail%20suggests%20the%20Army%20helicopter%20was%20flying%20above%20200%20feet%20(61%20meters)%2C%20the%20maximum%20altitude%20for%20the%20route%20it%20was%20using.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreliminary%20data%20indicates%20the%20control%20tower's%20radar%20showed%20the%20helicopter%20at%20200%20feet%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20accident%2C%20though%20officials%20said%20the%20information%20has%20not%20been%20confirmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20our%20job%20is%2C%20to%20figure%20that%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20NTSB%20board%20member%20Todd%20Inman%20told%20reporters%20when%20asked%20what%20could%20explain%20the%20discrepancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInman%20also%20said%20at%20Saturday's%20briefing%20that%20the%20helicopter's%20training%20flight%20would%20typically%20include%20the%20use%20of%20night-vision%20goggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20not%20know%20at%20this%20time%20if%20the%20night-vision%20goggles%20were%20actually%20being%20worn%2C%20nor%20what%20the%20setting%20may%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFurther%20investigation%20should%20be%20able%20to%20let%20us%20know%20if%20that%20occurred%20and%20what%20factor%20it%20may%20play%20in%20the%20overall%20accident.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20confirms%20that%20the%20air%20traffic%20controller%20alerted%20the%20helicopter%20to%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20CRJ700%20about%20two%20minutes%20before%20the%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20second%20before%20impact%2C%20the%20crew%20aboard%20the%20American%20flight%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bverbal%20reaction%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20plane's%20cockpit%20voice%20recorder%2C%20and%20flight%20data%20shows%20the%20plane's%20nose%20began%20to%20rise%2C%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20said%20an%20automated%20radio%20transmission%20alerted%20%26quot%3Btraffic%2C%20traffic%2C%20traffic%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20heard%20on%20the%20voice%20recorder%20and%20then%20sounds%20of%20the%20collision%20were%20heard%20before%20the%20recording%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20previously%20identified%20the%20other%20two%20soldiers%20killed%20in%20Wednesday's%20crash%20as%20Staff%20Sergeant%20Ryan%20Austin%20O'Hara%2C%2028%2C%20and%20Chief%20Warrant%20Officer%202%20Andrew%20Loyd%20Eaves%2C%2039.%20The%20names%20of%20the%2060%20passengers%20and%20four%20crew%20members%20who%20died%20on%20the%20jet%20have%20not%20been%20officially%20released%2C%20although%20many%20have%20been%20identified%20through%20family%20and%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECrews%20are%20preparing%20to%20remove%20the%20wreckage%20of%20the%20aircraft%20from%20the%20Potomac%20River%20starting%20on%20Sunday.%20Forty-two%20bodies%20have%20been%20recovered%20thus%20far%2C%20the%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20fire%20department%20said%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738462800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fd13mi6ig_washington-crash-soldier_625x300_02_February_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fstar-in-our-lives-soldie