n%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20alleges%20that%20members%20of%20the%20Global%20Alliance%20for%20Responsible%20Media%20(GARM)%2C%20a%20now-defunct%20initiative%20from%20the%20advertiser%20trade%20body%20the%20World%20Federation%20of%20Advertisers%20(WFA)%2C%20illegally%20conspired%20to%20%26quot%3Bcollectively%20withhold%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20advertising%20revenue%26quot%3B%20from%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20WFA%2C%20CVS%20Health%2C%20Mars%2C%20%C3%98rsted%2C%20and%20Twitch%20are%20the%20other%20defendants%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20WFA%20declined%20to%20comment.%20The%20trade%20body%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fad-group-to-suspend-garm-initiative-following-elon-musk-lawsuit-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20it%20planned%20to%20contest%20the%20suit%20and%20that%20it%20was%20confident%20in%20its%20adherence%20to%20competition%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EX%2C%20Nestl%C3%A9%2C%20Abbott%20Laboratories%2C%20Colgate%2C%20Lego%2C%20Pinterest%2C%20Tyson%20Foods%2C%20and%20Shell%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20which%20were%20sent%20outside%20normal%20US%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%202019%2C%20GARM%20was%20a%20US-based%20initiative%20that%20aimed%20to%20provide%20common%20frameworks%20to%20be%20used%20by%20media%20owners%2C%20advertisers%2C%20and%20agencies%20to%20categorize%20harmful%20content%20such%20as%20hate%20speech%2C%20misinformation%2C%20and%20online%20piracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20uptake%20of%20the%20frameworks%20was%20voluntary%2C%20and%20many%20online%20platforms%20and%20agencies%20adopted%20them%20as%20what%20became%20known%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bbrand%20safety%20floor%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20content%20that%20was%20deemed%20unsuitable%20for%20advertising%20to%20fund%20or%20appear%20next%20to.%20X%20was%20also%20previously%20a%20member%20of%20GARM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C