%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We%20retired%20early%20and%20moved%20to%20Ecuador.%20The%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20healthcare%20are%20more%20affordable%2C%20but%20there%20are%20challenges.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stephen%20and%20Joanna%20Vargha%20on%20a%20hike%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679c2538eb4be2fff9a308e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStephen%20and%20Joanna%20Vargha%20moved%20from%20North%20Carolina%20to%20Cuenca%2C%20Ecuador%2C%20in%202020%20after%20they%20retired.%3Cp%3EStephen%20and%20Joanna%20Vargha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EStephen%20and%20Joanna%20Vargha%20moved%20to%20Ecuador%20from%20North%20Carolina%20after%20retiring%20early.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20moved%20to%20Cuenca%20for%20its%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20vibrant%20culture%2C%20and%20welcoming%20expat%20community.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20recommend%20retiring%20abroad%20but%20said%20anyone%20thinking%20about%20it%20should%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20research.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Stephen%20and%20Joanna%20Vargha%2C%20a%20married%20couple%20who%20moved%20from%20North%20Carolina%20to%20Cuenca%2C%20Ecuador%2C%20in%202020%20after%20retiring%20early.%20Cuenca%20is%20located%20in%20the%20Andes%20mountains%20and%20has%20a%20population%20of%20about%20600%2C000%20people.%20Their%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStephen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20heard%20about%20Cuenca%2C%20Ecuador%2C%20as%20a%20place%20to%20retire%20way%20back%20in%202010.%20I%20checked%20it%20out%20for%20a%20week%20in%202011%20and%20visited%20some%20people%20I%20knew%20there.%20But%20I%20was%20only%2053.%20So%20I%20put%20it%20in%20the%20back%20of%20my%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%202019%2C%20my%20work%20was%20taking%20a%20toll%20on%20me%20physically%20and%20mentally.%20I%20had%20worked%20at%20a%20television%20station%20in%20North%20Carolina%20for%20over%2037%20years.%20We%20already%20had%20a%20retirement%20house%20in%20a%20small%20mountain%20town%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20so%20we%20decided%20to%20move%20there.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20plan%20was%20to%20leave%20my%20job%20and%20look%20for%20a%20one%20at%20half%20the%20pay%20because%20we%20could%20afford%20it.%20But%20after%20several%20months%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20couldn't%20get%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20realized%20the%20Affordable%20Care%20Act%20coverage%20was%20going%20to%20cost%20around%20%241%2C900%20a%20month%20for%20the%20two%20of%20us%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20we%20were%20too%20young%20for%20Medicare.%20I%20didn't%20work%20my%20butt%20off%20for%20four%20decades%20to%20give%20my%20hard-earned%20money%20to%20the%20insurance%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20Joanna%20goes%2C%20%26quot%3BLet's%20move%20to%20Cuenca.%26quot%3B%20This%20is%20a%20woman%20who%20had%20never%20been%20there%2C%20doesn't%20like%20big%20cities%2C%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20town%20of%20maybe%2075%2C000%20people%20when%20she%20left.%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BAre%20you%20sure%3F%26quot%3B%20But%20that's%20what%20we%20did.%20So%20I%20decided%20to%20retire%20at%2061%20when%20we%20moved%20to%20Ecuador.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoanna%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20retired%20around%20the%20same%20time%20at%2056%2C%20and%20before%20that%20worked%20for%20an%20auto%20insurance%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20talking%20about%20moving%20to%20Cuenca%20in%20May%20of%202019.%20We%20visited%20in%20September%20and%20looked%20at%20places.%20We%20moved%20in%20January%202020%20and%20just%20barely%20missed%20the%20pandemic%20lockdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221401%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Above%20image%20of%20Cuenca%2C%20Ecuador%2C%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679c26257bb3f854015b4685%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22934%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECuenca%20is%20considered%20an%20arts%20capital%20of%20Ecuador.%3Cp%3EStephen%20and%20Joanna%20Vargha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fa5488ed-e03f-4681-a9e9-3a1ccdc35dcf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECuenca%20is%20a%20great%20city%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20expats%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStephen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20You%20make%20friends%20so%20easily%20here.%20I've%20visited%2029%20countries%2C%20and%20I%20can%20emphatically%20say%20that%20the%20people%20in%20Cuenca%20are%20the%20friendliest%20people%20I%20have%20ever%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoanna%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20have%20made%20so%20many%20dear%20friends%20here%20that%20we%20would%20never%20have%20back%20home.%20We%20would've%20had%20to%20stay%20working%20and%20been%20too%20busy.%20Now%20we%20do%20three-hour%20lunches%20here%20just%20catching%20up%20and%20having%20fun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20so%20many%20things%20to%20do%20here%2C%20including%20art%20events%20and%20going%20to%20restaurants.%20There%20are%20lots%20of%20musical%20events.%20We%20have%20a%20free%20symphony%20and%20it's%20fabulous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStephen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Cuenca%20is%20becoming%20more%20of%20an%20international%20city.%20It's%20considered%20the%20arts%20capital%20of%20Ecuador%20and%20is%20called%20the%20%26quot%3BAthens%20of%20Ecuador%26quot%3B%20because%20of%20its%20culture%20and%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20speak%20a%20little%20Spanish%2C%20so%20we%20try%20to%20respect%20their%20culture%20and%20speak%20Spanish%20when%20we%20can%2C%20but%20some%20people%20here%20also%20speak%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStephen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20are%20an%20estimated%208%2C000%20to%2010%2C000%20foreigners%20living%20in%20Cuenca%2C%20mostly%20from%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%2C%20with%20Europe%20at%20a%20distant%20number%20three.%20Facebook%20groups%20are%20a%20great%20way%20to%20meet%20people%20and%20the%20expat%20community%20is%20very%20helpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoanna%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20You%20rely%20on%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223fef38f4-56b4-4290-99ee-43a54435a77e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20so%20much%20lower%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStephen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It's%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20compared%20to%20a%20good%20portion%20of%20the%20US%2C%20like%20with%20housing%20and%20food.%20Our%20electric%20and%20water%20bills%20are%20much%20lower.%20Healthcare%20here%20is%20very%20affordable%20and%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoanna%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20are%20some%20health%20things%20that%20you%20can't%20get%20done%20here.%20You%20have%20to%20go%20to%20Quito%2C%20about%20one%20hour%20away%2C%20or%20back%20to%20the%20states.%20But%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20here%20that%20you%20can%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20pallet%20of%2030%20farm-fresh%20eggs%20is%20like%20%244.25%20here.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFresh%20produce%20at%20the%20market%20is%20also%20affordable.%20To%20ride%20a%20bus%20is%2031%20cents.%20A%20taxi%20across%20the%20city%20could%20cost%20you%20%246%20including%20tip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20expats%20don't%20even%20own%20cars%20because%20it's%20very%20walkable.%20We%20walk%20everywhere.%20It's%20the%20healthiest%20we've%20ever%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStephen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20average%2035%20miles%20a%20week.%20It%20didn't%20take%20long%20for%20me%20to%20lose%20my%20American%20weight%2C%20as%20I%20call%20it.%20I%20went%20from%20192%20to%20168%20%E2%80%94%20just%20by%20the%20fresher%20food%2C%20better%20food%2C%20and%20walking%20all%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20great%20respect%20for%20older%20folks%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20just%20a%20cultural%20thing%2C%20it's%20part%20of%20the%20country's%20laws.%20There%20are%20discounts%20for%20older%20people%2C%20including%20on%20taxes%2C%20and%20even%20separate%20lines%20at%20the%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Streets%20of%20Cuenca.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679c2670eb4be2fff9a308ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECuenca%2C%20Ecuador%2C%20has%20become%20a%20draw%20for%20expats%20from%20the%20US%20and%20Canada.%3Cp%3EStephen%20and%20Joanna%20Vargha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStephen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20One%20drawback%20about%20Cuenca%20is%20there's%20not%20an%20international%20airport.%20We%20usually%20have%20to%20fly%20to%20Quito.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommunication%20can%20be%20terrible%20with%20vendors%20and%20government%20entities.%20Finding%20real%20estate%20listings%20is%20a%20little%20more%20difficult%20here%2C%20but%20we%20went%20to%20a%20real%20estate%20agent%20and%20she%20found%20our%20place%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20certain%20things%20you%20just%20can't%20buy%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoanna%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20When%20we%20go%20back%20to%20the%20US%20to%20visit%20we%20load%20up%20our%20suitcases%20with%20stuff%20to%20bring%20back%20with%20us.%20But%20that's%20changing%20literally%20every%20day.%20They're%20offering%20more%20stuff%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d7e35401-e247-4928-a546-34fd5936a7eb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20recommend%20retiring%20abroad%20but%20do%20your%20research%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStephen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20For%20people%20thinking%20about%20moving%20abroad%2C%20research%20is%20the%20most%20important%20thing.%20Facebook%2C%20blogs%2C%20get%20more%20than%20one%20source%20and%20make%20sure%20they're%20reliable.%20Definitely%20visit%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoanna%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETry%20to%20make%20some%20local%20contacts%20who%20you%20can%20talk%20to%20because%20they'll%20help%20you%20ease%20into%20local%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20we%20would%20never%20suggest%20doing%20the%20visa%20process%20on%20your%20own.%20You%20need%20a%20visa%20lawyer%20or%20a%20facilitator%20to%20help%20you%20because%20the%20rules%20can%20change%20quickly.%20It%20wasn't%20hard%20to%20do%20with%20the%20help.%20We%20used%20a%20group%20in%20Ecuador%20called%20Visa%20Angels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoanna%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20don't%20plan%20to%20leave%20Ecuador%20soon%2C%20but%20we%20are%20researching%20end-of-life%20continuous%20care%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStephen%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20may%20eventually%20have%20to%20move%20back%20to%20the%20US%20despite%20the%20high%20healthcare%20costs%20because%20they%20just%20don't%20have%20the%20same%20assisted%20living%20facility%20options%20here.%20But%20right%20now%2C%20we're%20very%20happy%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoanna%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20the%20five%20years%20we've%20been%20here%2C%20we've%20had%20a%20pandemic%2C%20national%20protests%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20droughts%20in%20Ecuador's%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20good%20and%20there's%20bad%20in%20any%20place%20that%20you%20live%2C%20but%20I%20like%20to%20say%20that%20when%20we%20knew%20we%20had%20to%20leave%20our%20home%2C%20we%20didn't%20make%20lemonade%20out%20of%20lemons.%20We%20made%20Limoncello%20and%20lemon%20pound%20cake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20such%20a%20wonderful%20adventure.%20I%20would've%20never%20dreamed%20that%20we%20would%20be%20able%20to%20do%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20news%20tip%20or%20a%20story%20to%20share%3F%20Are%20you%20an%20American%20who%20has%20moved%20abroad%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akvlamis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ekvlamis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3